Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1\uc0\u8260 2 pound French green lentils (lentilles du Puy)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1\uc0\u8260 4 cup good olive oil, plus extra for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salmon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 salmon}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups chopped yellow onions\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups chopped leeks, white and light green parts only\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/thyme/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 thyme}} leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 kosher salt}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}3\uc0\u8260 4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon minced fresh garlic\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1\uc0\u8260 2 cups chopped celery (4 stalks)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1\uc0\u8260 2 cups chopped carrots (3 carrots)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1\uc0\u8260 2 cups Homemade {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/stock/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Chicken Stock}}, recipe follows, or good canned {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/broth/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 broth}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons tomato paste\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons good red wine {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vinegar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vinegar}}\cf2 \
\pard\tx560\pardeftab720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Place the lentils in a heat-proof bowl and cover with boiling water. Set aside for 15 minutes, then {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/drain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 drain}}.\
Meanwhile, heat the oil in a saute pan, add the onions, leeks, thyme, salt, and pepper and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, until the onions are translucent. Add the garlic and cook for 2 more minutes. Add the drained lentils, celery, carrots, chicken stock, and tomato paste. Cover and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simmer}} over low heat for 20 minutes, until the lentils are tender. Add the vinegar and season, to taste.\
\
