\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Homemade Chicken Stock\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3 (5-pound) chickens\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 large onions, unpeeled and quartered\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 carrots, unpeeled and halved\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 celery stalks with leaves, cut in thirds\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 parsnips, unpeeled and cut in 1/2, optional\
{\listtext	\'95	}20 sprigs fresh flat-leaf {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsley/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 parsley}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}15 sprigs fresh thyme\
{\listtext	\'95	}20 sprigs fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dill/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 dill}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 head garlic, unpeeled and cut in 1/2 crosswise\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons whole black peppercorns\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Place the chickens, onions, carrots, celery, parsnips, parsley, thyme, dill, garlic, salt, and peppercorns in a 16 to 20-quart stockpot with 7 quarts of water and bring to a boil. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/skim/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Skim}} the surface, as needed. Simmer uncovered for 4 hours. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Strain}} the entire contents of the pot through a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/colander/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 colander}}, discarding the chicken and vegetables, and chill. Discard the hardened fat, and then pack the broth in quart containers.\
Yield: 6 quarts\cf2 \
